text: Thanks to our dedicated high-end tech personnel, we have regained full control of the Discord server within a few hours after the attack. Out of an abundance of caution, we had initially advised everyone to leave the server.

As you all know, community has been one of our core values. Why? It’s because of the humanity that’s found within us. Let’s embrace it by helping each other out during this time to build stronger than ever. Remember, riders…we are all #Anero

Thank you🌹
Riders, your support means the world to us; we cannot express this enough. Please stay patient, as our team is working hard behind the scenes for the new server.

We have a thorough vetting process of onboarding (interview, must be doxxed, full name with contact, etc.). For this incident, it appears as if one of the Discord management persons has been either hacked or is attempting to scam. We have good reason to believe it is the former.

We are taking further measures to demonstrate our high security and quality standards to ensure that everyone feels safe and comfortable. There will be absolutely NO minting until we accomplish this. It is our promise.

Here’s some context we wanted to provide with the incident:

We will be replacing it with an even more robust, state-of-the-art server.

As our brand is becoming more recognized in this space, it is also becoming the target of meticulous con artists. This behavior will NOT be tolerated and we are NOT intimidated by this incident.

We are here for everyone who has been compromised by the Discord hackers. A total of ~5Ξ has been stolen from our riders. If you have been affected, please send us with the appropriate proof — you WILL be refunded in full. 

Please leave the current Discord server immediately.

Our Discord has been compromised. 

Please do NOT click any links while we are getting this sorted out.
